Hetty is a [DS3000](http://www.hetzner.de/hosting/produkte_rootserver/ds3000/) dedicated server supplied by [Hetzner online](http://www.hetzner.de). 50 EUR (~40GBP) a month

* [Hetzner status and fault reports](http://translate.google.com/translate?hl=de&langpair=de|en&u=http://www.hetzner-status.de)
* [Hetzner wiki](http://wiki.hetzner.de/) with a [Debian section](http://wiki.hetzner.de/index.php/Debian)

Originally configured with a minimal Debian 64 bit etch and now upgraded to Debian's lenny release.

The 2 x 400 GB will be configured as software [RAID-1](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RAID-1#RAID_1) for redundancy.

There are two other machines that are used by Webconverger Limited:

* jurupa - webconverger.com at [Dreamhost](http://www.dreamhost.com/r.cgi?104617) in California - 120USD (~75GBP) a year
* au - webconverger.org a Xen 512-slice VPS hosted by [Slicehost](http://www.slicehost.com/) in Missouri (root) - 38USD a month (22.56GBP)

Hetty (88.198.3.35) is rented for the following functions:

* Performing [builds](http://build.webconverger.org/)
* Storage & backup (au only has 20G!)
* Providing a European mirror - [Webconverger.org mirror](http://hetty.webconverger.org/)
* Providing a European work place for developers

## Bootloader

From a hetzner installed etch and upgrading to lenny, lilo is claimed to be
installed via debconf. Though in fact **grub** is used if you use the
[KVM](http://lara01.rz3.hetzner.de/auth.asp).

## Notes on setup

Originally I tried to manually install Debian lenny via a
[guide](http://www.madscience.dk/index.php/2008/01/22/remote-ubuntu-install/) I
found on the net. Do not do it this way. There are lots of pitfalls.

Instead open a [Support-Anfragen](https://robot.your-server.de/server_3.php)
and ask politely for a minimal install with RAID-1. Finally it should look
